<BaseLayout title="Exotic Pet Laws in New Jersey">
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">New Jersey Exotic Pet Laws</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">In New Jersey, many exotic animals are regulated. Axolotls, ferrets, and Fennec foxes are currently restricted or require special permits.</p>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Allowed Species with Permits</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
    <li>Ferrets – require a permit from Fish & Wildlife.</li>
    <li>Some reptiles – depending on species and quantity.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Prohibited Species</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
    <li>Axolotls – illegal to own.</li>
    <li>Capybaras – illegal to own.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Resources</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">For the most current regulations, visit the New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection website.</p>
</BaseLayout>